00:00:10.310 --> 00:00:11.713 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Agnes.

00:00:12.279 --> 00:00:14.314 position:27% line:83% align:start
Please stay calm
and hear me out.

00:00:14.448 --> 00:00:17.317 position:7% line:89% align:start
My word dear, you look so pale.

00:00:17.986 --> 00:00:19.486 position:16% line:89% align:start
Is something the matter?

00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:21.321 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:00:22.690 --> 00:00:24.057 position:27% line:89% align:start
Oh, I can guess!

00:00:24.191 --> 00:00:25.459 position:27% line:89% align:start
You wasted money

00:00:25.593 --> 00:00:26.928 position:13% line:83% align:start
buying something frivolous
again, right?

00:00:27.060 --> 00:00:28.663 position:30% line:89% align:start
It's just fine.

00:00:28.796 --> 00:00:31.498 position:7% line:83% align:start
You know I've never gotten mad
at you over things like that!

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:33.868 position:35% line:83% align:start
All right.
So, what did you get me?

00:00:34.602 --> 00:00:36.336 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
I'm so very sorry.

00:00:36.470 --> 00:00:37.839 position:41% line:83% align:start
[AGNES]
Tell me, dear.

00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:40.808 position:16% line:83% align:start
Agnes, there's a new girl
in my life!

00:00:41.776 --> 00:00:43.043 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:00:46.113 --> 00:00:47.447 position:24% line:89% align:start
Please forgive me.

00:00:47.582 --> 00:00:49.316 position:33% line:89% align:start
Oh. [laughs]

00:00:49.449 --> 00:00:52.419 position:10% line:83% align:start
I suppose this sort of thing
happens all the time, right?

00:00:52.554 --> 00:00:54.789 position:7% line:89% align:start
Though, it is rather shocking.

00:00:54.923 --> 00:00:56.758 position:35% line:89% align:start
[thunders]

00:00:56.891 --> 00:00:59.861 position:13% line:83% align:start
I didn't mean for any of it
to transpire the way it did

00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:03.363 position:24% line:83% align:start
but I couldn't seem
to resist such a strong will.

00:01:03.497 --> 00:01:07.100 position:30% line:83% align:start
Oh, is that so?
Tell me all about this girl.

00:01:07.234 --> 00:01:09.837 position:35% line:83% align:start
Of course.
She's truly beautiful,

00:01:10.572 --> 00:01:12.507 position:10% line:89% align:start
With an impeccable pedigree.

00:01:13.608 --> 00:01:16.978 position:21% line:83% align:start
Really? Then I assume
she must be quite a charmer?

00:01:17.110 --> 00:01:18.513 position:35% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
And she's a twin, too!

00:01:20.982 --> 00:01:22.550 position:21% line:89% align:start
Have you gone insane?

00:01:22.684 --> 00:01:25.419 position:10% line:83% align:start
Agnes, stop it! I should have
asked for your permission first.

00:01:25.553 --> 00:01:27.187 position:16% line:83% align:start
What? Why would you think
I'd ever agree

00:01:27.321 --> 00:01:28.556 position:19% line:89% align:start
to something like that?

00:01:28.690 --> 00:01:31.425 position:33% line:83% align:start
Um, well, Pas
has no objection to it,

00:01:31.559 --> 00:01:33.995 position:13% line:83% align:start
and I think she's more than
an acceptable fiancÃ©e

00:01:34.127 --> 00:01:35.295 position:27% line:89% align:start
for our dear son.

00:01:35.429 --> 00:01:37.832 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hm! Wait, Pas what?

00:01:37.966 --> 00:01:40.068 position:27% line:89% align:start
He? He agreed to?

00:01:40.200 --> 00:01:41.636 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:01:41.769 --> 00:01:44.438 position:7% line:83% align:start
[CASSEROLE] What did you think
I was talking about?

00:01:44.572 --> 00:01:47.207 position:13% line:83% align:start
[AGNES] I thought you were
confessing to an affair.

00:01:47.341 --> 00:01:50.878 position:5% line:89% align:start
Father, how is Mother taking it?

00:01:51.946 --> 00:01:55.215 position:13% line:83% align:start
-She might need some time.
-So, she's really in shock?

00:01:56.183 --> 00:01:58.586 position:24% line:83% align:start
I expect it to last
at least a month.

00:01:58.720 --> 00:01:59.954 position:41% line:89% align:start
[cries]

00:02:00.088 --> 00:02:03.825 position:13% line:83% align:start
Another beautiful daughter?
I can't wait to meet her!

00:02:05.927 --> 00:02:08.596 position:13% line:83% align:start
[NARRATOR] This is the tale
of a genius pÃ¢tissier

00:02:08.730 --> 00:02:10.865 position:16% line:83% align:start
whose dream of making the
world's greatest dessert

00:02:10.999 --> 00:02:12.132 position:30% line:89% align:start
was cut short.

00:02:12.265 --> 00:02:13.968 position:27% line:83% align:start
Now, reincarnated
into another realm

00:02:14.102 --> 00:02:15.503 position:13% line:89% align:start
as the son of a poor noble,

00:02:15.637 --> 00:02:19.107 position:19% line:83% align:start
he pursues a world full
of desserts and smiles!

00:02:19.239 --> 00:02:22.510 position:13% line:83% align:start
A tale that's syrupy sweet,
chock full of yummy treats

00:02:22.644 --> 00:02:25.079 position:33% line:83% align:start
and sprinkled
with bitter darkness.

00:02:25.212 --> 00:02:27.715 position:7% line:89% align:start
A pastry chef, who was reborn,

00:02:27.849 --> 00:02:30.384 position:19% line:83% align:start
and dreams of creating
this new world's

00:02:30.518 --> 00:02:32.887 position:16% line:89% align:start
very own land of sweets!

00:04:05.012 --> 00:04:07.648 position:38% line:83% align:start
[COATON]
Count Retes! Your Ladyship!

00:04:09.617 --> 00:04:11.953 position:30% line:83% align:start
You're so loud.
What could it be?

00:04:12.086 --> 00:04:15.923 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's the heir to House Morteln.
He's just become engaged!

00:04:16.057 --> 00:04:17.558 position:47% line:89% align:start
Uh!

00:04:17.692 --> 00:04:18.793 position:7% line:83% align:start
[COATON] He's been matched with
one of Margrave Hubarek's

00:04:18.926 --> 00:04:20.094 position:24% line:89% align:start
younger daughters!

00:04:20.228 --> 00:04:21.461 position:21% line:89% align:start
How's that possible?

00:04:21.596 --> 00:04:23.463 position:27% line:83% align:start
That impoverished
backwater knight,

00:04:23.598 --> 00:04:25.233 position:10% line:89% align:start
joining the Margrave's house?

00:04:25.365 --> 00:04:27.502 position:44% line:89% align:start
Ugh!

00:04:30.071 --> 00:04:32.173 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RETES]
That'll leave a blood red stain.

00:04:32.305 --> 00:04:33.473 position:30% line:89% align:start
[clear throat]

00:04:33.608 --> 00:04:35.777 position:27% line:83% align:start
Why, I apologize
for startling you.

00:04:35.910 --> 00:04:39.046 position:41% line:83% align:start
Go on.
Which of his daughters is it?

00:04:39.180 --> 00:04:43.316 position:16% line:83% align:start
Uh! She's the fourth one,
Licorice Mille Hubarek.

00:04:43.450 --> 00:04:45.586 position:21% line:83% align:start
Twin sister to Petra,
who was recently engaged

00:04:45.720 --> 00:04:49.023 position:21% line:83% align:start
to a different noble,
Duke Kadlecek's grandson Squale.

00:04:49.157 --> 00:04:51.893 position:7% line:83% align:start
[RETES] She's the one involved
in the recent kidnapping.

00:04:52.026 --> 00:04:55.196 position:7% line:83% align:start
That's right. It appears to be
an engagement

00:04:55.328 --> 00:04:58.199 position:10% line:83% align:start
to prove her innocence in the
wake of the abduction incident.

00:04:58.331 --> 00:04:59.934 position:38% line:83% align:start
At least,
that's the vulgar rumor

00:05:00.067 --> 00:05:01.002 position:21% line:89% align:start
people are spreading.

00:05:01.869 --> 00:05:02.603 position:41% line:89% align:start
I see.

00:05:03.204 --> 00:05:05.006 position:19% line:83% align:start
[COATON] Do you suppose
there's any possibility

00:05:05.139 --> 00:05:06.974 position:16% line:83% align:start
that the Hubareks intend
to wait a few years

00:05:07.108 --> 00:05:10.310 position:24% line:83% align:start
until the memory of
all this drama has faded away,

00:05:10.443 --> 00:05:12.814 position:33% line:83% align:start
and dissolve
the engagement at that time?

00:05:13.881 --> 00:05:15.917 position:7% line:89% align:start
I don't think that's the case.

00:05:16.584 --> 00:05:18.753 position:27% line:83% align:start
Hubarek must have
another motive.

00:05:18.886 --> 00:05:20.955 position:24% line:83% align:start
Is it to set others
at ease regarding

00:05:21.088 --> 00:05:22.355 position:13% line:89% align:start
their family's intentions?

00:05:22.489 --> 00:05:24.826 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh! That makes sense!

00:05:24.959 --> 00:05:27.494 position:27% line:83% align:start
Once they joined
with Margrave Kadlecek's house,

00:05:27.628 --> 00:05:30.731 position:16% line:83% align:start
the sway of House Hubarek
grew significantly stronger.

00:05:31.398 --> 00:05:35.069 position:13% line:83% align:start
Indeed. Binding their house
to a minor one like Moreteln

00:05:35.203 --> 00:05:36.737 position:13% line:89% align:start
is quite a strategic move.

00:05:36.871 --> 00:05:39.439 position:13% line:83% align:start
Essentially making the case
he has no further intentions

00:05:39.574 --> 00:05:42.043 position:16% line:83% align:start
of gaining power through
marriage politics.

00:05:42.176 --> 00:05:43.611 position:27% line:89% align:start
Truly impressive.

00:05:43.744 --> 00:05:46.214 position:5% line:83% align:start
[RETES] It's exactly the kind of
thing that shrewd man

00:05:46.346 --> 00:05:47.515 position:30% line:89% align:start
would think of.

00:05:47.648 --> 00:05:49.217 position:13% line:89% align:start
And there's one more thing.

00:05:49.349 --> 00:05:50.818 position:19% line:89% align:start
Though it is small now,

00:05:50.952 --> 00:05:53.154 position:27% line:83% align:start
he sees potential
in the Fief of Morteln,

00:05:53.287 --> 00:05:56.157 position:7% line:83% align:start
to grow into a bountiful land,
on par with my own.

00:05:56.290 --> 00:05:57.992 position:38% line:83% align:start
[COATON]
That could never happen!

00:05:58.125 --> 00:05:59.694 position:33% line:89% align:start
But what if.

00:05:59.827 --> 00:06:02.797 position:10% line:83% align:start
When that wasteland was first
granted to him twenty years ago,

00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:06.200 position:10% line:83% align:start
it was a trap to ensure young
Lord Casserole's failure.

00:06:06.334 --> 00:06:09.637 position:10% line:83% align:start
I've heard it took them years
to produce their first harvest.

00:06:09.770 --> 00:06:11.706 position:5% line:89% align:start
Though, in the past three years,

00:06:11.839 --> 00:06:13.541 position:21% line:83% align:start
they've reduced their
wheat yield,

00:06:13.674 --> 00:06:16.577 position:10% line:83% align:start
and began to cultivate beans.
The result?

00:06:16.711 --> 00:06:19.347 position:7% line:83% align:start
By using the abundance of beans
as fertilizer

00:06:19.479 --> 00:06:20.715 position:21% line:89% align:start
to nourish the soil,

00:06:20.848 --> 00:06:23.416 position:27% line:83% align:start
they've improved
subsequent wheat harvests.

00:06:23.551 --> 00:06:24.986 position:27% line:89% align:start
That's brilliant.

00:06:25.119 --> 00:06:27.588 position:21% line:83% align:start
And who do you think
was behind that bright idea?

00:06:27.722 --> 00:06:29.290 position:19% line:83% align:start
Could it not have been
the suggestion

00:06:29.422 --> 00:06:31.125 position:10% line:89% align:start
of that silver-haired child?

00:06:31.259 --> 00:06:32.459 position:38% line:83% align:start
[COATON]
Impossible!

00:06:32.593 --> 00:06:35.196 position:38% line:83% align:start
You know
he's only nine years old, right?

00:06:35.329 --> 00:06:36.898 position:10% line:89% align:start
Yes well, have you forgotten

00:06:37.031 --> 00:06:40.501 position:5% line:83% align:start
when they came here to negotiate
compensation for the bandits?

00:06:41.535 --> 00:06:43.237 position:19% line:83% align:start
I was surprised to find
that Lord Morteln

00:06:43.371 --> 00:06:46.207 position:30% line:83% align:start
was not the one
conducting the negotiations,

00:06:46.340 --> 00:06:47.942 position:27% line:89% align:start
it was his child.

00:06:48.075 --> 00:06:50.978 position:10% line:83% align:start
And I'll admit he completely
got the better of me.

00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:54.882 position:13% line:89% align:start
There's no room for doubt.

00:06:55.016 --> 00:06:58.019 position:10% line:83% align:start
That sly old fox has noticed
the boy's potential.

00:06:58.719 --> 00:07:00.588 position:16% line:89% align:start
I've been outmaneuvered.

00:07:04.091 --> 00:07:05.826 position:38% line:89% align:start
[humming]

00:07:10.497 --> 00:07:11.732 position:44% line:83% align:start
[PAS]
There we go!

00:07:11.866 --> 00:07:13.834 position:24% line:83% align:start
All right Lord Pas,
that should be it!

00:07:13.968 --> 00:07:15.803 position:7% line:89% align:start
Great, thank you for your help!

00:07:16.404 --> 00:07:18.506 position:10% line:89% align:start
Hey Pas, what's in all these?

00:07:18.639 --> 00:07:19.974 position:35% line:89% align:start
Is it food?

00:07:20.107 --> 00:07:22.310 position:33% line:83% align:start
Duke Kadlecek
and his grandson, Lord Squale,

00:07:22.442 --> 00:07:23.644 position:5% line:89% align:start
have sent the goods I asked for!

00:07:23.778 --> 00:07:25.379 position:13% line:83% align:start
I've been waiting for them
to arrive!

00:07:25.513 --> 00:07:27.081 position:7% line:89% align:start
During their engagement party,

00:07:27.214 --> 00:07:29.083 position:21% line:83% align:start
I got them to promise
to help our fief

00:07:29.216 --> 00:07:31.218 position:24% line:83% align:start
and give us the aid
we need to grow!

00:07:31.886 --> 00:07:34.522 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Aah!
-Uh?

00:07:34.655 --> 00:07:36.489 position:24% line:83% align:start
-[LUMI] What is it?
-[MARC] A bush?

00:07:36.624 --> 00:07:40.661 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's a black locust sapling
also known as pseudo acacia.

00:07:40.795 --> 00:07:43.698 position:21% line:83% align:start
Okay. So, can we put
this thing in a recipe?

00:07:43.831 --> 00:07:45.266 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm afraid not.

00:07:45.399 --> 00:07:47.601 position:7% line:83% align:start
We could make a bunch of black
locust pie, couldn't we?

00:07:47.735 --> 00:07:50.404 position:16% line:83% align:start
Well, if I did, you sure
wouldn't want to eat it.

00:07:50.538 --> 00:07:51.471 position:47% line:89% align:start
Um!

00:07:51.605 --> 00:07:52.707 position:38% line:89% align:start
[laughs]

00:07:52.840 --> 00:07:54.608 position:35% line:83% align:start
-But wait.
-For what?

00:07:54.742 --> 00:07:56.644 position:27% line:83% align:start
[PAS] These trees
are really easy to grow,

00:07:56.777 --> 00:07:59.479 position:19% line:83% align:start
even in infertile soil,
and they provide nectar!

00:07:59.613 --> 00:08:01.282 position:38% line:83% align:start
-They do?
-And that's good?

00:08:01.415 --> 00:08:05.019 position:21% line:83% align:start
You see, their nectar
plus some bees makes honey!

00:08:05.152 --> 00:08:07.555 position:41% line:83% align:start
[BOTH]
Honey? The sweet stuff?

00:08:07.688 --> 00:08:09.623 position:38% line:83% align:start
It makes
everything taste so good.

00:08:09.757 --> 00:08:11.559 position:13% line:89% align:start
Yes, the sweetest of stuff!

00:08:11.692 --> 00:08:13.728 position:30% line:83% align:start
It's been such
an indispensable ingredient

00:08:13.861 --> 00:08:15.696 position:30% line:83% align:start
to the creation
of confectionary delights

00:08:15.830 --> 00:08:17.732 position:33% line:83% align:start
across time,
that any place with a history

00:08:17.865 --> 00:08:20.067 position:13% line:83% align:start
of desserts always involves
beekeeping!

00:08:20.201 --> 00:08:21.535 position:41% line:83% align:start
[BOTH]
Whoa!

00:08:21.669 --> 00:08:23.137 position:24% line:89% align:start
We'll raise trees!

00:08:23.270 --> 00:08:26.707 position:21% line:83% align:start
We'll get that honey,
then we'll eat all the sweets!

00:08:26.841 --> 00:08:28.309 position:30% line:89% align:start
Yep, that's it!

00:08:28.442 --> 00:08:29.844 position:41% line:83% align:start
[BOTH]
Hooray!

00:08:29.977 --> 00:08:32.279 position:21% line:83% align:start
Of course, there are
some real challenges

00:08:32.413 --> 00:08:34.115 position:7% line:89% align:start
with raising them on our land.

00:08:34.248 --> 00:08:35.449 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, yeah?

00:08:35.583 --> 00:08:38.085 position:27% line:83% align:start
Oh, I bet I know!
Soil and water, right?

00:08:38.219 --> 00:08:40.554 position:33% line:83% align:start
That's right!
Brilliant deduction, Lumi!

00:08:40.688 --> 00:08:43.758 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Oh!
-My grandfather taught me that.

00:08:44.225 --> 00:08:46.927 position:16% line:83% align:start
[PAS] The Fief of Morteln
gets little precipitation.

00:08:47.061 --> 00:08:48.863 position:19% line:83% align:start
So, any trees we plant
tend to die

00:08:48.996 --> 00:08:50.664 position:24% line:83% align:start
before they're able
to fully grow.

00:08:51.365 --> 00:08:54.168 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MARC] How are we gonna
get 'em water, then?

00:08:54.301 --> 00:08:56.103 position:16% line:89% align:start
With a shifting of gears.

00:08:56.237 --> 00:08:58.406 position:30% line:83% align:start
I don't really
know what that means.

00:08:58.539 --> 00:09:00.041 position:10% line:89% align:start
Is it something you can eat?

00:09:00.174 --> 00:09:04.111 position:16% line:83% align:start
Afraid not! It just means
we have to change our approach.

00:09:05.346 --> 00:09:06.580 position:21% line:89% align:start
But there are sweets

00:09:06.714 --> 00:09:08.783 position:19% line:83% align:start
created from a shifting
of gears as well.

00:09:08.916 --> 00:09:11.485 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Uh!
-So, what should we change?

00:09:11.652 --> 00:09:14.622 position:13% line:83% align:start
[PAS] Rather than imitating
lands with plentiful rainfall,

00:09:14.755 --> 00:09:16.390 position:16% line:83% align:start
I think I've got a better
strategy,

00:09:16.525 --> 00:09:19.126 position:30% line:83% align:start
we'll grow them
the same way arid regions do.

00:09:19.827 --> 00:09:21.896 position:7% line:89% align:start
Okay, but what does that mean?

00:09:23.397 --> 00:09:25.232 position:7% line:89% align:start
We're gonna build a reservoir!

00:09:25.366 --> 00:09:26.767 position:27% line:89% align:start
A razzle bar, eh?

00:09:26.901 --> 00:09:29.103 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Can we...
-You can't eat it.

00:09:29.670 --> 00:09:31.205 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's used to collect water.

00:09:31.338 --> 00:09:34.241 position:16% line:83% align:start
If it's big it'll last us
all year long,

00:09:34.375 --> 00:09:37.178 position:10% line:83% align:start
even during the early spring
when it's usually dry.

00:09:37.311 --> 00:09:38.513 position:27% line:89% align:start
And what's more,

00:09:38.646 --> 00:09:40.381 position:19% line:83% align:start
I chose this relatively
undeveloped land

00:09:40.515 --> 00:09:42.883 position:33% line:83% align:start
because it's
the perfect place for it to go!

00:09:43.717 --> 00:09:45.152 position:38% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE]
After taking out expenses,

00:09:45.286 --> 00:09:46.787 position:35% line:83% align:start
the profits
on the sale of textiles

00:09:46.921 --> 00:09:48.756 position:5% line:89% align:start
comes out to eight silver coins.

